{"TopicId":160001,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"How to create/rearrange categories in VAB","CreatedByName":"Waxing_Kibbous","CreatedById":151611,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-30T20:28:27Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Waxing_Kibbous","CreatedById":151611,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-30T20:28:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to know how to make a new category in the main categories bar in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E and move parts, as in remove from one category and place into another, into it. I\u0027ve poked around some mods that kind of do it, eg Kerbalism (makes it\u0027s own unique category), but I\u0027m not finding the appropriate code. My end game is to separate out plane parts from rocket parts, these tabs get way too bloated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-30T21:30:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi this mod does pretty much what you require.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/93955-122-filter-extensions-28-dec-18/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=1604157\u0026amp;embedComment=1604157\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Crzyrndm","CreatedById":92871,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-01T06:01:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr if you want to do it in code yourself, primary category creation is \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Crzyrndm/FilterExtension/blob/master/FilterExtension/CategoryInstance.cs#L59-L63\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and deletion is \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Crzyrndm/FilterExtension/blob/master/FilterExtension/Editor.cs#L75-L76\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-01T06:02:21Z\u0022 title=\u002205/01/2017 06:02  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 1, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Crzyrndm\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ShotgunNinja","CreatedById":159391,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-01T07:03:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn addition to what already said, you could take a look at \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/146758-12x-partorganizer-110/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EPartOrganizer\u003C/a\u003E. You can use that mod\u00A0directly\u00A0(see Adding a category example in its\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E), or even mess with the minimal source code \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ShotgunNinja/PartOrganizer/blob/master/src/PartOrganizer.cs\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(relevant logic is in\u00A0\u003Cem\u003EPartOrganizer::setup()\u003C/em\u003E method).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}